00:34:58.900 --> 00:35:00.950
fact that it's a low-malaria
region.

00:35:00.950 --> 00:35:03.500
And it turns out-- but this is
what is very important--

00:35:03.500 --> 00:35:06.190
it turns out that the price
is related to the

00:35:06.190 --> 00:35:08.020
incidence of malaria.

00:35:08.020 --> 00:35:12.260
So here, for example, in the
two-region case, I have given

00:35:12.260 --> 00:35:15.220
the bed net for free
in the region where

00:35:15.220 --> 00:35:16.410
the malaria was high.

00:35:16.410 --> 00:35:19.420
And the reason is because if I'm
a good policy maker and I

00:35:19.420 --> 00:35:21.700
don't have that much money,
that's what I will do.

00:35:21.700 --> 00:35:24.350
I will first give the bed net
for free in the region where

00:35:24.350 --> 00:35:25.980
malaria is high.

00:35:25.980 --> 00:35:28.680
And I will ask people to pay for
the bed net in the region

00:35:28.680 --> 00:35:30.910
where malaria is low.

00:35:30.910 --> 00:35:35.220
So what I observe in reality
is the demand for free bed

00:35:35.220 --> 00:35:38.360
nets in the high-malaria region
