00:36:27.110 --> 00:36:31.340
So if you compare within a line
the yellow to the red

00:36:31.340 --> 00:36:34.080
dot, you get the effect
of the price.

00:36:34.080 --> 00:36:39.000
If you compare across columns
within the same color, you get

00:36:39.000 --> 00:36:43.240
the effect of being in high-
versus low-malaria region.

00:36:43.240 --> 00:36:45.870
And you see they tend to go in
the same direction, which is

00:36:45.870 --> 00:36:49.180
what creates your bias.

00:36:49.180 --> 00:36:52.820
All right, do you get the

00:36:52.820 --> 00:36:55.150
